                <p class="us-essay">
                    At Team Annapurna, we're fueled by a mission to combat food waste and nourish those in need. We act
                    as a bridge between hotels with surplus food and a network of dedicated NGOs and volunteers. Here's
                    how we make a difference:
                    <br><br>
                    Hotels, by their very nature, can generate significant food waste. We believe this perfectly good
                    food shouldn't go to landfill. Instead, we connect hotels with local NGOs actively serving
                    communities. This allows hotels to safely donate leftover meals to shelters, soup kitchens, and
                    other programs providing vital food assistance. Team Annapurna fosters a collaborative network of
                    volunteers who play a crucial role in the food rescue process. By partnering with us, hotels gain a
                    valuable tool for responsible waste management while enhancing their social responsibility profile.
                    NGOs receive a reliable source of nutritious meals, allowing them to focus their resources on other
                    vital services. Volunteers are empowered to make a real difference in the fight against hunger.
                    <br><br>
                    Team Annapurna is a growing movement dedicated to building a society where leftover food becomes a
                    lifeline for those in need. We invite hotels, NGOs, and passionate volunteers to join us. Together,
